<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-718-962  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 718 962.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  August 6 1990 n281 p48(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft ups the ante; new LAN strategy goes head-to-head withNovell.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>McPartlin, John P.; Garvey, Martin; Myers, Kara.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Microsoft hopes to upset Novell's 70 percent hold on the networkmarket by slowly developing its own market share.andP;  One part ofMicrosoft's plan is the $60 million Network Specialist Program,which will approve 600 US resellers and 400 resellers outside theUS as authorized dealers in the next year and increase Microsoft'snetwork sales and support staff by 400 in 1991.andP;  The other aspectof the plan is the introduction of networking software, such asLAN Manager 2.0 and SQL (Structured Query Language) Server 1.1.andO;Analysts say Microsoft holds the advantage for OS/2 users, who mayadopt the OS/2-based LAN Manager over industry leader Novell'sNetWare.andP;  Novell executives say they are ready for Microsoft'schallenge and feel their market domination is insurmountable.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (marketing).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Product:   LAN Manager 2.0 (Network management software) (marketing)SQL Server 1.1 (Data base management system) (marketing).andO;Topic:     Marketing StrategyLocal Area NetworksSoftware PackagesStrategic PlanningCompetitionDealers and AgentsMarket Share.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>